title: 'easy, fun Haskell for music : find all the easy divisions of an interval'
pid: 187c2035-12ad-401d-b0c3-af4be228652d
body: |2-
  Given a ratio of integers a:b,
  find all (a*n, b*n) pairs
  such that both products are leass than a threshold (35?),
  and find all integers between a*n and b*n,
  and report the entire triplet.
misc:
- Had_ID_Before_Import
